 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Gameplay Designer id Software 4 reviews Dallas, TX id Software 4 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Overview 
Do you obsess over how long the telegraph on an AI attack should be? Do you fire a weapon in a game and break down why it feels so good to shoot? Do you play the latest game modes and think about why they work or why they don’t? If you are the type of person who lives and breathes how it  feels  to play games, then you’ve come to the right place.
 We are seeking a talented  GAMEPLAY DESIGNER  to come help us make industry-leading weapons, AI, progression systems, player mechanics, and game modes for AAA first-person action games. You will work closely with Game Directors, fellow Designers, and multi-discipline feature teams to help plan, prototype, and build systems that players will enjoy for years to come.
 Responsibilities 
Work closely with the game director and design leads to execute on the vision for the game 
Use your creativity to execute on design goals and solve design challenges that push our games forward 
Create detailed and easy to follow design documentation 
Participate in brainstorm sessions, refine, and execute on ideas within a schedule 
Use our proprietary toolset to craft and execute on game features from prototype to shipping quality 
As a feature owner, collaborate with artists, engineers and other designers to execute on design implementation and problem solving 
Collaborate and provide feedback to leadership and other members of the team to continuously improve our products 
Work with directors and leads as we review the success of current systems and initiatives as well as brainstorm new solutions 
Qualifications 
In-depth knowledge of recent id games 
Excellent written and verbal communication skills 
Experience working with a variety of established game toolsets 
Experience working in a collaborative environment with cross disciplinary groups 
Ability to work proactively as part of a team 
Strong presentation skills and the ability to present that information to audiences 
Prefer a minimum of 3 years of experience working in a design capacity on PC or console games 
Prefer experience shipping a AAA game or patching/maintaining a live game 
Candidate must be willing to take a short design test 
 We embrace diversity, equity, and inclusion in everything we do – from recruiting for our studios, publishing and operations to fostering safe and respectful workplaces that encourage collaboration. Our culture is based on principles of respect, inclusion, and fair treatment and we welcome anyone into our family without regard to race, religion, gender identity, sexual orientation, or age. 
 Our diversity fuels our innovation and inspires us to create game worlds that bring us closer to the global community of players we serve. ZeniMax Media Inc. 30+ days ago original job Report job You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Jobs at id Software in Dallas, TX Company Info Follow Get job updates from id Software id Software 4 reviews Id Software (/ɪd/; see Company name, sometimes erroneously capitalized as ID Software) is an American video game development company with... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
 
